This paper deals with machine learning approaches for solving time-dependent partial differential equations (PDEs), which is a topic that falls under the category of numerical analysis (cs.NA). The paper specifically uses a fully convolutional LSTM network, which is a type of neural network architecture commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL), suggesting that it may also fall under those categories. Additionally, the paper involves training the network on simulation data, which is a common approach in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of finite-difference and finite-volume methods, which are commonly used in computational engineering (cs.CE) and scientific computing (cs.SI).
